I am a gradual student in UT-Austin's CS program, and I run a
weekly <a href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/adams/hh-page.html">happy hour</a> for the department.<p>

This is my only claim to fame, my undergraduate thesis.  I specified
the type rules and an operational semantics of the OO core of C++.
It's available as a gzipped <a href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/adams/c++thesis.dvi.gz">dvi file</a>
or a gzipped <a href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/adams/c++thesis.ps.gz">postscript file</a>.  Let me know
what you think of it.<p>

